    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-03-31T09:55:30+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-31T09:55:30+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-30T23:25:30Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-30T23:25:30Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system over the Tasman sea extends a weak ridge over SA. A trough over central WA extends over southwest SA, and is forecast to move across the west and south later Tuesday, pushing into the northeast of SA on Wednesday. Another high pressure system is expected to become established south of the Bight late in the week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW012" description="Lower Eyre Peninsula" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-03-31T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-01T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-30T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-31T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Becoming cloudy. Very high chance of showers in the late afternoon and evening. The chance of a thunderstorm in the late afternoon and evening. Winds northerly 25 to 40 km/h turning west to northwesterly 25 to 35 km/h in the afternoon. Daytime maximum temperatures in the low 30s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:30am to 4:30pm, UV Index predicted to reach 7 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-01T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-02T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-31T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-01T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Slight chance of a shower in the early morning. Mostly sunny day. Winds westerly 15 to 25 km/h tending southwesterly in the late afternoon then becoming light in the late evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 14 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-02T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-03T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-01T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-02T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog. Light winds becoming southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the day then tending southerly during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 10 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-03T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-04T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-02T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-03T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog. Slight chance of a shower near the east coast in the morning and afternoon. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 11 and 14 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
